WEBVTT

00:01:38.920 --> 00:01:39.720
You're awake.

00:01:41.400 --> 00:01:42.160
Are you okay?

00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:44.120
You should consider yourself lucky.

00:01:44.120 --> 00:01:45.080
You almost lost

00:01:45.479 --> 00:01:47.160
your life in the Gobi Desert.

00:01:47.560 --> 00:01:48.490
Have some water.

00:01:50.120 --> 00:01:51.240
Is your foot okay?

00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:53.160
My foot is fine.

00:01:53.640 --> 00:01:54.800
And I'm fine too.

00:01:55.560 --> 00:01:57.490
It's just that my shoes are ruined.

00:01:57.759 --> 00:01:59.360
But I have a new discovery.

00:02:00.080 --> 00:02:01.040
What discovery?

00:02:01.440 --> 00:02:03.500
The Gobi exclusive limited edition,

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:04.880
tape leather shoes.

00:02:05.640 --> 00:02:06.280
Look.

00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:09.160
Name brand plus tape, a fashionable mix-and-match style.

00:02:09.160 --> 00:02:10.889
The only one in the entire Gobi.

00:02:11.960 --> 00:02:13.480
I'm not throwing these shoes away.

00:02:13.480 --> 00:02:15.080
I'll keep them as a souvenir.

00:02:15.120 --> 00:02:16.160
You really shouldn't throw them away.

00:02:16.160 --> 00:02:17.420
Keep them to remind you

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:18.860
not to show off.

00:02:27.120 --> 00:02:27.760
Yan.

00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:29.640
Where are we?

00:02:30.960 --> 00:02:32.440
Yangdaman Primary School.

00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:33.600
The sandstorm isn't over yet.

00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:35.079
We'll leave early tomorrow morning.

00:02:35.079 --> 00:02:36.280
Looking around here,

00:02:36.880 --> 00:02:38.740
why is there an assembled rocket?

00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:43.120
The school used to have a hobby group

00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:46.520
started by a volunteer teacher from a big city.

00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:48.500
The students really liked it.

00:02:49.120 --> 00:02:50.050
But the thing is,

00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:52.370
it's too harsh here to keep people.

00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:53.680
Before the rocket was even finished,

00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:54.680
the teacher left.

00:02:58.200 --> 00:02:58.880
Oh, right.

00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:00.360
Just ahead of the school

00:03:00.360 --> 00:03:02.080
are the earliest ruins of Yangdaman.

00:03:02.080 --> 00:03:03.210
Yangdaman Village,

00:03:03.560 --> 00:03:06.080
the one established by Kashi Station in 1968,

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:07.480
that Yangdaman Village?

00:03:07.840 --> 00:03:08.440
Yes.

00:03:09.120 --> 00:03:11.440
I've heard the elders at the station talk about it.

00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:12.320
Back then,

00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:15.440
there was a shortage of food and water,

00:03:15.440 --> 00:03:16.900
and the weather was harsh.

00:03:18.079 --> 00:03:19.960
Under such tough conditions,

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:22.079
our first generation of aerospace workers

00:03:22.079 --> 00:03:23.240
actually shouted the slogan,

00:03:23.240 --> 00:03:25.200
'Work while alive, accept death when it comes,

00:03:25.200 --> 00:03:27.760
bury our loyal bones in Yangdaman.'

00:03:27.760 --> 00:03:28.620
Listen to this,

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:32.420
is there any prouder declaration than this?

00:03:32.920 --> 00:03:34.600
They built the camp,

00:03:34.600 --> 00:03:36.200
organized production,

00:03:36.200 --> 00:03:38.000
and studied and trained at the same time.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:39.720
They drank water from stagnant pools

00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:41.720
and slept in underground shelters.

00:03:42.480 --> 00:03:45.280
Winter nights were long and cold.

00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:48.290
When there wasn't enough food,

00:03:48.440 --> 00:03:50.840
they used alfalfa to satisfy their hunger.

00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:52.960
When the sandstorms blew outside,

00:03:52.960 --> 00:03:54.240
you couldn't see a person

00:03:54.240 --> 00:03:55.520
five meters away.

00:03:55.800 --> 00:03:57.840
With heads held high and feet firmly planted,

00:03:57.840 --> 00:04:00.000
they reached for the stars and competed with the heavens.

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:00.930
What kind of gods

00:04:02.120 --> 00:04:04.120
were they?

00:04:09.200 --> 00:04:11.400
They were ordinary people just like us.

00:04:11.880 --> 00:04:12.840
Young folks.

00:04:16.560 --> 00:04:17.160
Yes,

00:04:18.519 --> 00:04:19.640
they were young,

00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:22.200
ordinary people.

00:04:24.840 --> 00:04:25.680
My teacher

00:04:26.680 --> 00:04:28.480
is buried in this Gobi Desert.

00:04:30.760 --> 00:04:33.360
He was just in his early forties when he passed.

00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:35.050
An ordinary person.

00:04:36.120 --> 00:04:37.080
He was

00:04:38.720 --> 00:04:39.720
shameless,

00:04:40.400 --> 00:04:41.400
loved to eat meat,

00:04:41.480 --> 00:04:43.280
and could never get enough beer.

00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:46.420
He'd feel terrible after drinking too much.

00:04:47.080 --> 00:04:47.720
Yan,

00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:49.180
that actually rhymes.

00:04:49.360 --> 00:04:50.600
Xinjiang rapper.

00:05:14.960 --> 00:05:15.840
Slow down.

00:05:21.320 --> 00:05:22.880
Mr. Yan,

00:05:23.360 --> 00:05:24.890
Principal Wang, come here.

00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:26.120
Well,

00:05:26.400 --> 00:05:28.360
take these three bottles of water to drink on the way.

00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:28.760
Okay? No,

00:05:28.760 --> 00:05:30.080
what are you doing?

00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:31.280
I told you to keep them.

00:05:31.280 --> 00:05:32.480
We're almost there.

00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:33.480
One more thing.

00:05:33.480 --> 00:05:35.960
The thing I asked you about last time,

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.560
about our supplies,

00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:39.080
please keep it in mind.

00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:40.400
Don't worry, Principal Wang.

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:42.159
I will definitely come when I have time in the next couple of days.

00:05:42.159 --> 00:05:43.120
Okay.

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:43.600
Keep them.

00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:44.080
Okay.

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:44.560
We are leaving.

00:05:44.560 --> 00:05:45.440
Thank you.

00:05:45.800 --> 00:05:48.120
Principal,

00:05:48.120 --> 00:05:50.120
let the scientists teach us how to make rockets.

00:05:50.120 --> 00:05:50.640
Please.

00:05:50.640 --> 00:05:51.000
Yeah.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:52.120
Everyone, quiet down.

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:53.040
Children,

00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:55.040
the scientists are researching rockets

00:05:55.040 --> 00:05:57.520
that will fly to the moon, you know?

00:05:57.520 --> 00:05:59.240
Let's not delay their work.

00:05:59.920 --> 00:06:00.920
Okay, let's go back to class.

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:01.640
We can play football after class.

00:06:01.640 --> 00:06:03.280
But I still want to see the rockets.

00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:04.840
Me too. I want to see the rockets too.

00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:06.080
Alright, children.

00:06:06.400 --> 00:06:07.880
I will first tell you

00:06:07.880 --> 00:06:09.480
the story of our Yangdaman.

00:06:09.880 --> 00:06:11.480
Do you know what our Yangdaman

00:06:11.480 --> 00:06:12.640
used to do?

00:06:12.640 --> 00:06:13.320
No.

00:06:13.320 --> 00:06:14.840
We will go and take a look together then.

00:06:14.840 --> 00:06:15.520
Okay?

00:06:15.920 --> 00:06:17.040
Let's go back to the classroom first.

00:06:17.040 --> 00:06:18.240
Okay.

00:06:18.720 --> 00:06:19.440
Children.

00:06:21.520 --> 00:06:22.000
Come.

00:06:23.920 --> 00:06:24.400
Come.

00:06:31.240 --> 00:06:34.040
Although I can't make rockets for you,

00:06:34.280 --> 00:06:36.240
But I can tell you stories about rockets.

00:06:36.240 --> 00:06:38.040
Really? Really?

00:06:38.640 --> 00:06:40.960
Astronauts don't lie to astronauts.

00:06:40.960 --> 00:06:44.680
Great.

00:06:44.680 --> 00:06:45.840
Awesome!

00:06:46.120 --> 00:06:47.800
Good.

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:49.880
That's great.

00:06:55.520 --> 00:06:56.480
Can I stay

00:06:56.480 --> 00:06:58.680
and be their extracurricular teacher?

00:07:04.480 --> 00:07:06.280
It won't interfere with my work.

00:07:07.920 --> 00:07:09.120
If you need anything,

00:07:09.200 --> 00:07:10.880
the station will fully support you.

00:07:10.880 --> 00:07:11.520
Thanks.

00:07:14.760 --> 00:07:15.480
Teacher,

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:16.880
when do we start?

00:07:17.120 --> 00:07:18.760
How do rockets succeed?

00:07:18.760 --> 00:07:20.080
Tell us stories about rockets.

00:07:20.080 --> 00:07:21.440
Are there aliens?

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:23.640
Teacher, please tell us.

00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:24.280
I want to build a rocket.

00:07:24.280 --> 00:07:25.360
Me too.

00:07:25.360 --> 00:07:26.560
Please tell us.

00:07:26.560 --> 00:07:28.360
Have you heard the story of 'Two Bombs, One Satellite'?

00:07:28.360 --> 00:07:30.520
No.

00:07:30.520 --> 00:07:31.720
Then today I'll tell you

00:07:31.720 --> 00:07:34.520
the story of our country's 'Two Bombs, One Satellite'.

00:07:34.520 --> 00:07:36.360
Good, good, good.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:09:03.360
Come on, come on, come on.

00:09:16.840 --> 00:09:21.080
We won.

00:09:21.560 --> 00:09:22.720
No. 4 Aerospace Flight Control Center.

00:09:22.720 --> 00:09:24.780
An aerospace flight control center.

00:09:33.840 --> 00:09:35.240
After Xiaonian, it's the New Year.

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:37.040
Hurry up and paste the couplets.

00:09:37.760 --> 00:09:40.360
The cafeteria is making lamb dumplings today.

00:09:40.480 --> 00:09:43.080
Let me see if double-sided tape is on this 'Fu' character.

00:09:43.080 --> 00:09:43.840
Slow down.

00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:44.320
Okay.

00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:46.120
Our 'Fu' character must be right side up.

00:09:46.120 --> 00:09:46.440
Wu.

00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:47.440
It can't be upside down.

00:09:47.440 --> 00:09:48.880
Help me pick up an expert later.

00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:49.720
What expert?

00:09:50.120 --> 00:09:51.160
For the joint test.

00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:51.960
Do I know them?

00:09:52.800 --> 00:09:53.840
No. Just go when you're told.

00:09:53.840 --> 00:09:55.120
Why so much nonsense?

00:09:55.120 --> 00:09:55.880
Go.

00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:07.640
Chu Jiajia.

00:10:29.760 --> 00:10:30.840
Long time no see.

00:10:30.840 --> 00:10:31.880
You don't call me Sister Jia anymore.

00:10:31.880 --> 00:10:33.480
You dare to call me by my name.

00:10:33.680 --> 00:10:35.680
You are not my boss anymore.

00:10:36.440 --> 00:10:38.970
So of course I have to change how I address you.

00:10:47.080 --> 00:10:48.410
What are you looking at?

00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:51.480
Just checking if it's really you.

00:10:51.880 --> 00:10:53.140
Have you confirmed it?

00:10:55.960 --> 00:10:57.360
You've gotten prettier.

00:11:00.720 --> 00:11:03.320
Then I must thoroughly

00:11:05.400 --> 00:11:06.400
examine you.

00:11:10.520 --> 00:11:11.640
Haven't your wings grown strong?

00:11:11.640 --> 00:11:13.400
Why are you still scared?

00:11:13.400 --> 00:11:15.280
No, I'm not.

00:11:17.960 --> 00:11:19.720
You came here so suddenly

00:11:19.720 --> 00:11:21.040
without giving us a heads-up.

00:11:21.040 --> 00:11:22.840
Why the surprise attack?

00:11:22.840 --> 00:11:23.560
Right,

00:11:23.840 --> 00:11:24.840
suddenly.

00:11:25.320 --> 00:11:26.760
I'm here to inspect your work.

00:11:26.760 --> 00:11:28.090
A surprise inspection.

00:11:29.560 --> 00:11:32.020
Now he's a top hand at the Deep Space Station,

00:11:32.400 --> 00:11:33.240
known as

00:11:33.240 --> 00:11:35.300
the Little Prince of the Gobi Desert.

00:11:37.480 --> 00:11:38.600
Besides work,

00:11:38.600 --> 00:11:41.260
should we also inspect the living environment?

00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:42.240
Of course.

00:11:42.720 --> 00:11:43.920
But before that,

00:11:43.920 --> 00:11:46.560
could I trouble our Little Prince

00:11:46.560 --> 00:11:48.280
to help me with my luggage?

00:11:52.760 --> 00:11:53.640
Where are you staying tonight?

00:11:53.640 --> 00:11:54.900
Did Old Yan arrange it?

00:11:55.800 --> 00:11:58.240
I'm staying in the dorm

00:11:58.240 --> 00:11:59.160
next to yours.

00:12:00.920 --> 00:12:01.980
What's for dinner?

00:12:02.480 --> 00:12:03.240
Can I order?

00:12:03.240 --> 00:12:05.160
Go ahead. I'll show you what I can do.

00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:07.280
Then I want Sichuan hot pot.

00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:08.760
When I was abroad,

00:12:08.760 --> 00:12:09.920
eating sandwiches every day,

00:12:09.920 --> 00:12:11.200
all I could think about was the spicy and flavorful

00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:12.760
Sichuan hot pot.

00:12:12.760 --> 00:12:13.680
I want mutton.

00:12:13.680 --> 00:12:15.160
I really want it.

00:12:15.160 --> 00:12:17.800
And duck blood, duck intestines,

00:12:17.800 --> 00:12:19.840
tripe, and aorta.

00:12:19.840 --> 00:12:21.400
And I want an oil dip.

00:12:21.400 --> 00:12:21.920
And...

00:12:28.240 --> 00:12:29.800
You had a hard time abroad.

00:12:32.280 --> 00:12:33.410
But this is Kashgar.

00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:35.600
We have plenty of mutton.

00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:37.920
Okay.

00:12:45.520 --> 00:12:46.760
Come on, help me out.

00:12:46.760 --> 00:12:47.520
Help out.

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:50.250
Is this okay?

00:12:50.880 --> 00:12:53.560
I borrowed all the Sichuan hot pot supplies

00:12:53.560 --> 00:12:55.690
in the entire Kashgar station for you.

00:12:56.480 --> 00:12:57.920
Nine-grid hot pot.

00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:00.040
Smells so good.

00:13:00.440 --> 00:13:01.440
Look what this is.

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:04.400
And mutton.

00:13:05.200 --> 00:13:06.120
I specifically asked the chef

00:13:06.120 --> 00:13:08.200
to save this aorta.

00:13:08.200 --> 00:13:10.080
Mr. Yan spent a fortune today.

00:13:10.080 --> 00:13:11.120
Of course.

00:13:11.120 --> 00:13:12.400
Thank you.

00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:14.930
And here are the duck intestines you ordered.

00:13:15.200 --> 00:13:16.760
Thanks, Mr. Yan.

00:13:16.760 --> 00:13:17.360
By the way,

00:13:17.920 --> 00:13:19.760
I'll get you some

00:13:19.760 --> 00:13:20.820
tender beef later.

00:13:21.720 --> 00:13:23.280
And these sweet and sour spare ribs.

00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:24.440
I have to take a picture for Ying Ziqi

00:13:24.440 --> 00:13:25.570
to make him jealous.

00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:27.840
Have a drink, Mr. Yan.

00:13:27.840 --> 00:13:28.600
Okay.

00:13:30.200 --> 00:13:31.720
Come on.

00:13:31.720 --> 00:13:32.680
Sit down.

00:13:34.080 --> 00:13:35.200
Let me propose a toast.

00:13:35.200 --> 00:13:36.280
Welcome.

00:13:36.280 --> 00:13:38.360
Thanks for your hard work today, Mr. Yan.

00:13:38.360 --> 00:13:39.600
We must complete the task

00:13:39.600 --> 00:13:40.760
assigned by Mr. Wu.

00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:46.720
I've heard so much about Ms. Chu.

00:13:46.720 --> 00:13:50.000
Back then, Sister Jia was the Great Demon King of flight control.

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:50.880
She took great pains

00:13:50.880 --> 00:13:52.920
to train me

00:13:52.920 --> 00:13:54.920
and tortured me a thousand times. Enough.

00:13:54.920 --> 00:13:56.400
You're acting again.

00:13:56.400 --> 00:13:57.240
There you go again.

00:13:57.240 --> 00:13:59.970
Aerospace people don't lie to aerospace people.

00:14:06.120 --> 00:14:07.080
Rest early.

00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:10.520
Let's stop here.

00:14:12.400 --> 00:14:13.860
You should rest early too.

00:14:28.120 --> 00:14:28.680
Wu Wei.

00:14:31.600 --> 00:14:33.060
After the mission is over,

00:14:33.880 --> 00:14:35.480
I have something to tell you.

00:14:35.800 --> 00:14:37.600
I have something to tell you too.

00:14:41.200 --> 00:14:41.860
Good night,

00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:43.120
Chu Jiajia.

00:14:45.280 --> 00:14:45.940
Good night,

00:14:46.600 --> 00:14:47.520
Mr. Wu.

00:15:08.440 --> 00:15:09.800
Good night, Mr. Wu.

00:15:09.800 --> 00:15:10.930
Good night, Old Yan.

00:15:12.480 --> 00:15:13.080
Let's go to sleep then.

00:15:13.080 --> 00:15:14.120
Going to sleep.

00:15:15.840 --> 00:15:16.680
Close the door.

00:15:16.680 --> 00:15:17.520
Right.

00:15:28.440 --> 00:15:29.120
Seventy.

00:15:33.800 --> 00:15:34.440
Alright,

00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:36.660
thanks for your hard work.

00:15:38.440 --> 00:15:40.440
How are you going to spend your holiday?

00:15:40.440 --> 00:15:41.960
I got a few new games.

00:15:41.960 --> 00:15:43.080
Let's play together then

00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:44.120
and break some records.

00:15:44.120 --> 00:15:45.120
I don't have time.

00:15:46.240 --> 00:15:48.640
What are you doing that you don't have time?

00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:51.000
I've been here for quite a while.

00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:52.530
I want to go back to Beijing.

00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:55.680
This holiday is only a few days.

00:15:55.680 --> 00:15:58.000
The round trip takes two days,

00:15:58.000 --> 00:15:59.600
and you still want to go back?

00:16:02.560 --> 00:16:03.160
Got it.

00:16:04.840 --> 00:16:05.840
What did they say?

00:16:06.680 --> 00:16:09.920
I turn the stars into you.

00:16:10.120 --> 00:16:13.160
I can't believe we've been apart for a year.

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:16.360
Young people.

00:16:16.600 --> 00:16:17.400
I understand.

00:16:27.640 --> 00:16:28.280
What?

00:16:34.920 --> 00:16:37.780
The deep space array signal reception test failed.

00:16:46.480 --> 00:16:47.340
What happened?

00:16:47.680 --> 00:16:48.920
Signal reception delay.

00:16:48.920 --> 00:16:50.450
Four transmission signals

00:16:50.600 --> 00:16:53.930
are still interfering with each other in different ranges.

00:16:59.320 --> 00:17:00.080
Stop.

00:17:00.320 --> 00:17:01.250
The test failed.

00:17:02.200 --> 00:17:02.800
Reset.

00:17:03.280 --> 00:17:04.880
Troubleshoot the cause immediately.

00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:06.280
Did you find the problem?

00:17:08.119 --> 00:17:09.319
This malfunction

00:17:09.760 --> 00:17:11.359
looks random.

00:17:12.079 --> 00:17:13.920
Although the test was fine just now,

00:17:13.920 --> 00:17:16.160
the alarm went off twice before.

00:17:17.319 --> 00:17:18.319
What's going on?

00:17:18.920 --> 00:17:20.560
Individual tests were fine.

00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:22.280
But there's an issue when arrayed.

00:17:22.280 --> 00:17:24.480
Could it be the synthesizer?

00:17:25.040 --> 00:17:26.520
We can't be misled by it.

00:17:27.040 --> 00:17:29.240
Our software has gone through many rounds of testing.

00:17:29.240 --> 00:17:31.640
Everything that should be checked has been checked.

00:17:31.640 --> 00:17:33.700
Not finding it is just a coincidence.

00:17:33.800 --> 00:17:35.280
Where on earth is it?

00:17:36.280 --> 00:17:38.540
Why is it impossible to find like a ghost?

00:17:38.640 --> 00:17:40.400
It's not like we have no direction.

00:17:40.400 --> 00:17:41.360
At least we can be sure

00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:44.290
to start troubleshooting from the software system.

00:17:46.760 --> 00:17:48.760
We can't rush.

00:17:49.360 --> 00:17:50.840
Tell me how not to worry.

00:17:51.120 --> 00:17:52.240
I swore

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:54.100
and made a solemn pledge for this.

00:17:54.440 --> 00:17:56.040
Before Flight Control solves the problem,

00:17:56.040 --> 00:17:57.800
we must finish the deep space arraying

00:17:57.800 --> 00:18:00.260
to ensure the following steps can continue.

00:18:09.440 --> 00:18:10.200
I'm sorry.

00:18:11.040 --> 00:18:12.320
I didn't mean to take it out on you.

00:18:12.320 --> 00:18:14.280
But we are running out of time.

00:18:14.560 --> 00:18:15.600
There are still many tasks ahead

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:17.530
that require the deep space array.

00:18:17.880 --> 00:18:19.040
Including Haoyue 5.

00:18:19.920 --> 00:18:22.450
Too many people are waiting for our good news.

00:18:22.880 --> 00:18:24.810
Whether we can successfully array

00:18:25.040 --> 00:18:27.160
is too important to us.

00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:29.240
We can't hold everyone back.

00:18:32.920 --> 00:18:33.720
I know.

00:18:38.680 --> 00:18:39.520
Actually,

00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:42.720
I have a solution.

00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:49.200
Okay, understood.

00:18:51.520 --> 00:18:52.600
We will cooperate.

00:18:56.960 --> 00:18:57.760
What's wrong?

00:19:01.800 --> 00:19:03.000
News from Beijing

00:19:03.680 --> 00:19:05.040
says the test failed.

00:19:05.040 --> 00:19:07.040
The parameters need to be redesigned.

00:19:07.040 --> 00:19:07.880
That means

00:19:08.800 --> 00:19:10.660
we are back to square one here too.

00:19:13.040 --> 00:19:13.720
Beijing.

00:19:19.720 --> 00:19:20.840
Qu Ruonan is here.

00:19:29.200 --> 00:19:30.480
We are at the apartment.

00:19:30.480 --> 00:19:31.760
You can settle in and get some rest first.

00:19:31.760 --> 00:19:32.280
Later,

00:19:32.280 --> 00:19:34.400
we will proceed with the tri-location joint test.

00:19:34.400 --> 00:19:34.960
This way.

00:19:35.280 --> 00:19:35.920
Thank you.

00:19:50.240 --> 00:19:50.800
Hello.

00:19:51.440 --> 00:19:52.320
Are you okay?

00:19:55.000 --> 00:19:55.920
I'm sorry.

00:19:56.200 --> 00:19:57.480
It's all my fault.

00:19:58.600 --> 00:20:01.240
I know your test was originally very successful.

00:20:01.240 --> 00:20:02.440
No one will blame you.

00:20:03.800 --> 00:20:04.600
I know.

00:20:05.320 --> 00:20:07.880
This is your first time working on a project independently,

00:20:07.880 --> 00:20:09.120
and you want to do your best.

00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:10.520
Don't be too stressed.

00:20:10.520 --> 00:20:12.720
We'll solve any problems together.

00:20:13.920 --> 00:20:14.920
Rest assured.

00:20:15.360 --> 00:20:17.520
Xu Xu and I will also hurry up.

00:20:19.560 --> 00:20:20.690
Look out the window.

00:20:25.240 --> 00:20:26.000
Here.

00:20:27.160 --> 00:20:28.000
Can you see me?

00:20:35.240 --> 00:20:36.040
Oh, right.

00:20:36.040 --> 00:20:37.640
Tonight is the Heart Comet.

00:20:39.320 --> 00:20:42.120
This comet is the brightest long-period comet

00:20:42.120 --> 00:20:43.760
that humans can observe

00:20:43.760 --> 00:20:45.520
since Hale-Bopp.

00:20:46.600 --> 00:20:47.840
Long period?

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:48.720
Yes.

00:20:49.480 --> 00:20:50.720
6,800 years.

00:20:52.560 --> 00:20:53.680
That's very rare.

00:20:54.760 --> 00:20:56.680
6,800 years.

00:20:58.120 --> 00:21:01.320
According to our human migration plan,

00:21:01.320 --> 00:21:03.480
humanity would have left Earth

00:21:03.480 --> 00:21:05.340
and built a Dyson sphere long ago.

00:21:06.440 --> 00:21:08.840
Sometimes when we look up at the starry sky,

00:21:09.480 --> 00:21:11.810
we always feel the stars are very far away.

00:21:12.080 --> 00:21:14.160
In fact, each of us is a star.

00:21:15.280 --> 00:21:17.120
The nitrogen in our DNA,

00:21:17.680 --> 00:21:19.160
the calcium in our teeth,

00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:20.920
the iron in our blood,

00:21:20.920 --> 00:21:22.560
and the carbon in our food

00:21:22.840 --> 00:21:24.480
were all made of stars that scattered

00:21:24.480 --> 00:21:26.400
after the Big Bang.

00:21:26.800 --> 00:21:28.200
So each of us

00:21:28.960 --> 00:21:30.000
is a star.

00:21:32.120 --> 00:21:35.160
So according to quantum entanglement,

00:21:35.440 --> 00:21:37.600
no matter how far apart we are,

00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:40.160
we will eventually be connected.

00:21:40.920 --> 00:21:42.600
A moment in time

00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:45.320
is actually right now, right?

00:21:45.840 --> 00:21:46.640
That's right.

00:21:48.800 --> 00:21:49.560
Ying Ziqi,

00:21:51.240 --> 00:21:52.770
let's make a wish together.

00:21:55.680 --> 00:21:56.240
Okay.

00:22:15.280 --> 00:22:16.040
I'm done.

00:22:16.600 --> 00:22:17.800
What did you wish for?

00:22:21.880 --> 00:22:23.560
Never mind. Don't tell me.

00:22:23.560 --> 00:22:25.240
It won't come true if you say it out loud.

00:22:25.240 --> 00:22:26.680
I think our wishes

00:22:28.080 --> 00:22:29.400
are the same.

00:22:30.160 --> 00:22:31.890
The most beautiful confession

00:22:32.440 --> 00:22:33.440
is normal.

00:22:33.960 --> 00:22:35.420
The most beautiful answer

00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:37.460
is understanding.

00:22:38.800 --> 00:22:39.480
Normal.

00:22:41.200 --> 00:22:41.930
Understood.

00:22:45.760 --> 00:22:46.520
Mr. Zhang,

00:22:46.760 --> 00:22:48.360
I know you're under a lot of pressure.

00:22:48.360 --> 00:22:49.240
I am too.

00:22:49.760 --> 00:22:52.290
But if this universe could be easily reached,

00:22:52.400 --> 00:22:53.880
would it still be the truth?

00:22:53.880 --> 00:22:56.080
We should also properly reset ourselves

00:22:56.080 --> 00:22:57.340
and reboot the system.

00:22:58.920 --> 00:22:59.880
Let it out.

00:23:00.960 --> 00:23:01.960
How?

00:23:01.960 --> 00:23:04.840
Roar like a dragon.

00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:06.320
Do you know how a dragon roars?

00:23:06.320 --> 00:23:06.920
How?

00:23:09.600 --> 00:23:10.560
Does it work?

00:23:10.560 --> 00:23:11.400
Give it a try.

00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:19.800
Feeling better?

00:23:19.800 --> 00:23:21.200
I think so.

00:23:22.720 --> 00:23:23.880
Where did I hear

00:23:23.880 --> 00:23:25.600
that dragon roar?

00:23:26.120 --> 00:23:27.000
It was a book.

00:23:27.360 --> 00:23:28.360
It had a pen.

00:23:28.360 --> 00:23:29.200
You tapped it,

00:23:29.200 --> 00:23:30.640
and it made a dragon roar.

00:23:31.120 --> 00:23:33.450
I think there were fish sounds too. Wu Wei.

00:23:33.880 --> 00:23:35.040
Actually,

00:23:35.680 --> 00:23:37.600
Chu Jiajia has always thought highly of you.

00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:39.200
I hope you don't let her down.

00:23:39.600 --> 00:23:40.560
I will do my best.

00:23:40.840 --> 00:23:42.640
I'm not just talking about work.

00:23:44.160 --> 00:23:45.800
I know how you feel about her

00:23:46.760 --> 00:23:48.560
and your fearless personality.

00:23:50.200 --> 00:23:52.120
I used to think I was like that too.

00:23:53.440 --> 00:23:55.600
But I still lost to reality and my ego.

00:23:57.080 --> 00:23:58.610
I hope you think it through.

00:23:59.360 --> 00:24:00.490
Think what through?

00:24:00.600 --> 00:24:01.240
A lot,

00:24:02.400 --> 00:24:04.330
including many practical issues.

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:07.240
To me,

00:24:09.240 --> 00:24:10.080
those are not problems.

00:24:10.080 --> 00:24:12.480
I hope you can hold on to this answer for ten years,

00:24:12.480 --> 00:24:14.720
twenty years, or even a lifetime.

00:24:15.480 --> 00:24:16.200
Mr. Zhang,

00:24:17.560 --> 00:24:19.800
I have thought about it clearly

00:24:19.800 --> 00:24:20.760
and seriously.

00:24:22.720 --> 00:24:23.800
But when you ask me,

00:24:24.120 --> 00:24:26.180
from what standpoint are you asking?

00:24:26.600 --> 00:24:28.040
Our work is very special.

00:24:29.360 --> 00:24:31.290
Sometimes during a mission phase,

00:24:31.560 --> 00:24:34.120
we might have to undergo months of closed training.

00:24:34.120 --> 00:24:35.720
We can't even use our phones.

00:24:36.520 --> 00:24:37.640
And sometimes,

00:24:37.640 --> 00:24:40.000
one person might have just returned from a mission,

00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:40.880
while the other

00:24:41.240 --> 00:24:42.960
has to start a new one.

00:24:44.040 --> 00:24:45.840
The love between two strong individuals

00:24:45.840 --> 00:24:47.680
needs to stand the test of time,

00:24:48.240 --> 00:24:51.400
overcoming loneliness, selfishness, and ego.

00:24:52.560 --> 00:24:54.290
I hope you can understand this.

00:24:56.040 --> 00:24:56.920
Mr. Zhang,

00:24:58.000 --> 00:24:59.330
the more I listen to you,

00:25:00.600 --> 00:25:03.460
the more it sounds like you're talking to yourself.

00:25:03.800 --> 00:25:05.530
Have you seen "Interstellar"?

00:25:06.680 --> 00:25:08.000
In the emotional world of human beings,

00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:10.130
there is something that truly exists.

00:25:11.080 --> 00:25:12.120
It is so powerful

00:25:12.400 --> 00:25:14.730
like gravitational waves in the universe

00:25:15.080 --> 00:25:18.140
that it can transcend the dimensions of time and space.

00:25:19.560 --> 00:25:20.560
It's unstoppable

00:25:21.720 --> 00:25:22.720
and unalterable.

00:25:26.600 --> 00:25:27.200
Yes.

00:25:27.840 --> 00:25:30.640
This sounds more like something I'd say to myself.

00:25:30.680 --> 00:25:33.120
The courage to break through all resistance,

00:25:33.120 --> 00:25:33.960
from you,

00:25:34.320 --> 00:25:35.250
I've learned it.

00:25:42.360 --> 00:25:43.480
Bye.

00:25:43.480 --> 00:25:45.140
Let's take another look here.

00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:15.080
I think I saw a ghost.

00:26:16.160 --> 00:26:16.800
Where?

00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:20.460
This ghost likes to play hide-and-seek with us.

00:26:22.320 --> 00:26:23.840
Since it's hiding deep,

00:26:23.840 --> 00:26:25.240
we'll dig deeper.

00:26:25.880 --> 00:26:28.960
We can tear the house down if we have to.

00:26:29.360 --> 00:26:30.440
I don't believe we won't find it.

00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:31.640
Do you have any ideas?

00:26:32.440 --> 00:26:34.480
I rechecked part of the program,

00:26:34.920 --> 00:26:37.080
and I found a problem with the underlying logic.

00:26:37.080 --> 00:26:38.810
The code can also be optimized.

00:26:40.080 --> 00:26:40.760
We might

00:26:43.960 --> 00:26:44.840
as well redo it.

00:26:46.840 --> 00:26:48.770
Tens of thousands of lines of code.

00:26:48.920 --> 00:26:50.600
Do you know what that means?

00:26:53.960 --> 00:26:54.560
I know.

00:26:55.840 --> 00:26:58.560
But I think it's right in the code.

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:01.400
Looking line by line,

00:27:02.240 --> 00:27:04.040
I don't believe we can't find it.

00:27:05.640 --> 00:27:07.320
Unless

00:27:07.320 --> 00:27:08.560
we have a better way.

00:27:13.400 --> 00:27:14.480
Mr. Qin once said,

00:27:15.240 --> 00:27:16.560
when you have no clue,

00:27:16.880 --> 00:27:17.600
a stupid method

00:27:17.600 --> 00:27:18.640
is a good method.

00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:19.760
Don't forget,

00:27:19.760 --> 00:27:22.690
our aerospace industry was calculated on abacuses.

00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:24.530
Then let's do it.

00:27:25.240 --> 00:27:26.570
We don't have much time.

00:27:26.960 --> 00:27:28.220
Let's assign the work.

00:27:28.440 --> 00:27:30.400
I haven't done any real work for months.

00:27:30.400 --> 00:27:31.600
My hands are itching.

00:28:31.680 --> 00:28:34.360
Ascender, orbiter, returner,

00:28:34.360 --> 00:28:35.920
claw-type rendezvous and docking,

00:28:35.920 --> 00:28:38.000
simulation test begins.

00:28:40.400 --> 00:28:40.880
This

00:28:40.880 --> 00:28:42.760
is Ms. Chu, whom I mentioned before.

00:28:42.760 --> 00:28:45.240
Happy.

00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:00.480
Final check.

00:29:00.840 --> 00:29:01.760
Final check.

00:29:03.040 --> 00:29:04.000
All normal.

00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:05.600
Orbital parameters normal.

00:29:20.960 --> 00:29:23.240
Now conducting the deep space antenna array

00:29:23.240 --> 00:29:24.900
multi-task acceptance test.

00:29:25.640 --> 00:29:27.360
Tianshan tracking normal.

00:29:27.360 --> 00:29:29.480
Now sending the wake-up command to the Haoyue-4 probe

00:29:29.480 --> 00:29:31.960
and Yuetu-2.

00:29:32.400 --> 00:29:33.240
Rabbit,

00:29:34.520 --> 00:29:36.400
I can finally talk to you.

00:29:40.120 --> 00:29:41.120
I announce that

00:29:41.120 --> 00:29:44.600
the simulated rendezvous test of the two spacecraft is successful.

00:29:44.600 --> 00:29:47.000
The Kashgar four 35-meter antenna array system

00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:48.000
has been successfully tested.

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:50.280
The TT&C system covers all frequency bands

00:29:50.280 --> 00:29:52.240
and is officially put into the Haoyue 5

00:29:52.240 --> 00:29:54.040
and Mars exploration missions.

00:30:00.920 --> 00:30:01.720
Great.

00:30:12.080 --> 00:30:12.740
Here you go.

00:30:14.720 --> 00:30:16.240
Since when do you like eating this?

00:30:16.240 --> 00:30:17.500
How come I didn't know?

00:30:18.120 --> 00:30:19.840
Didn't the test fail before?

00:30:19.840 --> 00:30:21.480
So I carried this around with me

00:30:21.480 --> 00:30:22.840
as my lucky charm.

00:30:22.840 --> 00:30:25.520
I didn't expect it to actually bring me good luck.

00:30:25.520 --> 00:30:26.320
What's wrong?

00:30:32.440 --> 00:30:33.920
You dropped this.

00:30:34.280 --> 00:30:35.080
It's not mine.

00:30:35.280 --> 00:30:37.140
But I remember you came in second.

00:30:37.600 --> 00:30:38.640
My mom said,

00:30:38.640 --> 00:30:40.320
getting second place is like getting nothing.

00:30:40.320 --> 00:30:41.360
How is that the same?

00:30:41.360 --> 00:30:43.920
It's second place in the National Math Olympiad.

00:30:43.920 --> 00:30:45.920
Many people want it but can't get it.

00:30:49.480 --> 00:30:50.810
I only want first place.

00:30:54.680 --> 00:30:55.480
I'm sorry.

00:30:56.440 --> 00:30:58.640
It's fine. I'm also in the primary school division,

00:30:58.640 --> 00:31:00.160
but I didn't win a prize.

00:31:00.160 --> 00:31:02.600
But I have a gold medal.

00:31:04.120 --> 00:31:04.760
Here.

00:31:12.360 --> 00:31:13.080
So sweet.

00:31:30.200 --> 00:31:30.840
So sweet.

00:31:37.520 --> 00:31:39.240
This place is really beautiful.

00:31:39.240 --> 00:31:39.880
Yeah.

00:31:40.200 --> 00:31:42.730
I come here for a walk when I have nothing to do.

00:31:44.680 --> 00:31:46.340
Do you come here to walk alone?

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:49.120
To get some fresh air,

00:31:49.120 --> 00:31:51.450
look at the stars, and think about things.

00:31:52.880 --> 00:31:53.880
Think about what?

00:31:55.200 --> 00:31:57.920
Like, before the Big Bang,

00:31:58.160 --> 00:32:00.320
when there was no time and no space,

00:32:00.720 --> 00:32:01.850
what exactly was it?

00:32:02.760 --> 00:32:05.160
And since the universe contains everything,

00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:06.890
why is it called 'outer space'?

00:32:08.280 --> 00:32:11.720
Also, where are the aliens,

00:32:11.720 --> 00:32:13.640
and why is Zhang Ziming so annoying?

00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:16.040
These two unsolved mysteries of humanity.

00:32:18.760 --> 00:32:21.440
You think about so many serious things,

00:32:21.960 --> 00:32:22.960
and you don't even have time

00:32:22.960 --> 00:32:23.960
to think about me?

00:32:27.160 --> 00:32:30.320
I did. I thought about you, but not completely.

00:32:31.840 --> 00:32:32.200
No,

00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:34.000
mainly because you weren't in front of me,

00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:36.960
so I couldn't think very specifically.

00:32:38.360 --> 00:32:40.400
Well, I'm in front of you now.

00:32:40.400 --> 00:32:42.730
You can think a little more specifically.

00:32:46.280 --> 00:32:47.340
It's specific now.

00:32:51.040 --> 00:32:53.680
I'm thinking about our past,

00:32:54.440 --> 00:32:56.160
present,

00:32:56.160 --> 00:32:57.040
and future.

00:32:57.840 --> 00:33:00.080
This entire, complete timeline.

00:33:01.680 --> 00:33:03.320
On this timeline,

00:33:04.360 --> 00:33:05.490
you were born first,

00:33:06.160 --> 00:33:07.220
and then I was born.

00:33:07.680 --> 00:33:09.400
We grew up separately,

00:33:09.400 --> 00:33:10.730
studied individually,

00:33:11.360 --> 00:33:12.520
and coincidentally

00:33:12.520 --> 00:33:14.380
both fell in love with aerospace.

00:33:15.640 --> 00:33:17.040
We met in flight control.

00:33:18.480 --> 00:33:21.640
You were the leader, senior, and the 'Great Demon King',

00:33:22.200 --> 00:33:24.440
and I was the subordinate, the rookie.

00:33:25.440 --> 00:33:27.560
Then we worked together,

00:33:27.560 --> 00:33:28.840
completed tasks together,

00:33:28.840 --> 00:33:30.480
went through low points together,

00:33:30.480 --> 00:33:31.880
and succeeded together.

00:33:31.960 --> 00:33:33.520
So many things,

00:33:33.520 --> 00:33:34.850
right up to the present.

00:33:35.760 --> 00:33:36.640
My orbit

00:33:37.400 --> 00:33:39.440
has long intersected with yours.

00:33:40.760 --> 00:33:42.420
It's universal gravitation.

00:33:42.840 --> 00:33:44.440
It's quantum entanglement.

00:33:45.120 --> 00:33:46.440
It will never change.

00:33:47.720 --> 00:33:50.120
Last time you texted me to come back alive,

00:33:50.600 --> 00:33:51.440
as an order,

00:33:51.920 --> 00:33:52.980
and I completed it.

00:33:53.560 --> 00:33:54.620
Where is my reward?

00:34:01.040 --> 00:34:02.360
I said before

00:34:03.280 --> 00:34:06.000
that I felt there was a distance between us.

00:34:08.080 --> 00:34:09.679
But I found out

00:34:09.679 --> 00:34:12.440
that in the face of liking someone,

00:34:13.800 --> 00:34:16.600
distance and things like that don't matter at all.

00:34:20.040 --> 00:34:21.080
I really hope

00:34:21.440 --> 00:34:23.120
I could be a star in the sky.

00:34:23.800 --> 00:34:25.760
If I could emit light and heat,

00:34:26.600 --> 00:34:28.440
I wouldn't be afraid of the dark.

00:34:30.440 --> 00:34:31.639
I also hope

00:34:33.520 --> 00:34:35.440
I could have a star of my own.

00:34:38.239 --> 00:34:40.480
If it could travel alongside me,

00:34:41.840 --> 00:34:43.639
I could

00:34:43.639 --> 00:34:44.960
face fears together

00:34:46.199 --> 00:34:47.460
and welcome the light.

00:34:52.920 --> 00:34:53.880
I...

00:34:54.960 --> 00:34:56.639
What's wrong? Are you scared?

00:34:56.639 --> 00:34:58.000
No, I'm not scared.

00:34:59.120 --> 00:34:59.680
I...

00:35:06.840 --> 00:35:07.760
Chu Jiajia.

00:35:08.600 --> 00:35:10.040
I want to be your star too,

00:35:11.280 --> 00:35:13.140
orbiting you as a companion star.

00:35:19.760 --> 00:35:21.620
Not orbiting as a companion star,

00:35:22.280 --> 00:35:24.160
but flying alongside.

00:35:27.480 --> 00:35:29.410
That mission will take a long time.

00:35:30.080 --> 00:35:31.280
How long will it take?

00:35:36.120 --> 00:35:37.450
As long as the universe.

00:36:13.360 --> 00:36:15.880
On this New Year's Eve,

00:36:16.240 --> 00:36:17.280
we take stock of

00:36:17.280 --> 00:36:20.800
the departing year of 2019.

00:36:22.600 --> 00:36:24.280
This one is broken.

00:36:24.280 --> 00:36:25.160
You...

00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:26.600
I...

00:36:26.680 --> 00:36:28.000
If you do it like this,

00:36:28.280 --> 00:36:28.760
what are we going to do?

00:36:28.760 --> 00:36:30.290
The filling will spill out.

00:36:30.400 --> 00:36:31.080
Look.

00:36:31.680 --> 00:36:34.240
Cup it in your palm like this.

00:36:34.240 --> 00:36:35.080
Then,

00:36:35.080 --> 00:36:36.400
pinch both sides,

00:36:36.920 --> 00:36:38.440
and press it like this.

00:36:38.440 --> 00:36:39.240
And it's done.

00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:41.130
That's impressive.

00:36:41.400 --> 00:36:42.880
Okay, I'll give it a try.

00:36:43.720 --> 00:36:46.040
Like this, then put some meat in.

00:36:48.800 --> 00:36:50.480
Let's see if your method works.

00:36:50.480 --> 00:36:51.120
Look.

00:36:51.480 --> 00:36:52.880
Isn't this a steamed bun?

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:54.920
Moon Rabbit.

00:36:55.760 --> 00:36:56.520
Moon Rabbit.

00:36:57.160 --> 00:36:58.200
Limited edition.

00:36:58.560 --> 00:36:59.360
For you.

00:36:59.760 --> 00:37:01.490
You're giving me a Moon Rabbit?

00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:05.560
Then I'll give you some lunar soil.

00:37:12.720 --> 00:37:14.240
I'll brush it off for you.

00:37:19.680 --> 00:37:22.000
How on earth do you do this?

00:37:22.120 --> 00:37:22.680
Here,

00:37:22.680 --> 00:37:23.760
I will teach you

00:37:23.760 --> 00:37:25.290
from your perspective now.

00:37:25.840 --> 00:37:27.280
First,

00:37:27.280 --> 00:37:28.560
open both hands,

00:37:28.560 --> 00:37:30.440
then cup your left hand a bit.

00:37:32.520 --> 00:37:34.050
Now comes the crucial part.

00:37:35.840 --> 00:37:36.970
Squeeze the middle,

00:37:37.320 --> 00:37:38.980
and then do this to both sides.

00:37:46.920 --> 00:37:47.760
Is that them?

00:37:47.760 --> 00:37:48.440
Yes.

00:37:50.560 --> 00:37:53.200
Look at our Mr. Qin.

00:37:55.080 --> 00:37:56.720
Mr. Gu, Mr. Qin.

00:37:56.720 --> 00:37:57.560
Say hello to everyone.

00:37:57.560 --> 00:37:58.890
Did you make dumplings?

00:37:59.000 --> 00:37:59.480
What's wrong?

00:37:59.480 --> 00:38:01.120
The dumplings Mr. Gu made for me.

00:38:01.120 --> 00:38:02.920
These dumplings look like steamed buns.

00:38:02.920 --> 00:38:04.600
There's no oil at all, look.

00:38:04.600 --> 00:38:06.860
Don't listen to him. They're delicious.

00:38:07.400 --> 00:38:09.720
Don't listen to his nonsense complaints.

00:38:09.720 --> 00:38:11.400
It's the doctor's orders

00:38:11.400 --> 00:38:13.240
to have less oil and salt.

00:38:13.840 --> 00:38:15.480
Less oil and salt is abusing the elderly.

00:38:15.480 --> 00:38:16.320
Mr. Qin.

00:38:16.320 --> 00:38:18.080
A real man knows when to yield.

00:38:18.320 --> 00:38:19.720
Hello, Mr. Qin and Mr. Gu.

00:38:20.920 --> 00:38:21.800
Mr. Qin, Mr. Gu.

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:22.520
Everyone's on duty.

00:38:22.520 --> 00:38:23.400
Come say hi, guys.

00:38:23.400 --> 00:38:24.800
Hello, Mr. Qin and Mr. Gu.

00:38:25.400 --> 00:38:26.280
Jia.

00:38:27.360 --> 00:38:29.360
You went all the way to Kashgar

00:38:29.360 --> 00:38:31.160
just to visit Wei?

00:38:31.160 --> 00:38:31.920
Really?

00:38:31.920 --> 00:38:32.760
Look.

00:38:35.200 --> 00:38:36.320
What do you mean, visit?

00:38:36.320 --> 00:38:37.320
I'm here for

00:38:37.320 --> 00:38:38.640
joint testing.

00:38:38.640 --> 00:38:39.720
I have a mission.

00:38:41.320 --> 00:38:43.160
Are you guys still on duty?

00:38:43.800 --> 00:38:45.240
We didn't go home this year.

00:38:45.240 --> 00:38:46.840
We're taking turns on shift.

00:38:47.000 --> 00:38:48.530
And you have big dumplings.

00:38:49.120 --> 00:38:50.640
Hello. I'm not late, am I?

00:38:50.640 --> 00:38:52.500
Happy New Year, Mr. Qin and Mr. Gu.

00:38:53.360 --> 00:38:54.560
Come on.

00:38:54.560 --> 00:38:55.960
It's almost the new year.

00:38:58.880 --> 00:38:59.960
Come on, let's have a toast.

00:38:59.960 --> 00:39:00.920
Let's do it together.

00:39:00.920 --> 00:39:01.960
Together.

00:39:02.440 --> 00:39:03.640
Countdown.

00:39:04.360 --> 00:39:07.040
Ten, nine,

00:39:07.040 --> 00:39:07.840
eight, seven,

00:39:08.840 --> 00:39:11.480
six, five, four,

00:39:11.480 --> 00:39:13.840
three, two!

00:39:15.000 --> 00:39:17.000
Happy New Year!

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:24.920
Happy New Year!

00:39:24.920 --> 00:39:26.680
Cheers.

00:39:26.680 --> 00:39:28.440
Go, Haoyue-5!

00:39:28.920 --> 00:39:30.240
Return victorious!

00:39:30.760 --> 00:39:31.820
See you in Beijing.

00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:37.040
Cheers!

00:39:43.200 --> 00:39:45.040
I'm so happy today.

00:39:45.040 --> 00:39:48.120
Our Muxing team is finally back together again.

00:39:48.120 --> 00:39:48.800
Wei.

00:39:48.800 --> 00:39:50.120
You have no idea.

00:39:50.120 --> 00:39:52.240
I missed you so much this past year.

00:39:52.240 --> 00:39:54.080
I missed you too.

00:39:55.120 --> 00:39:56.480
Let's skip the small talk.

00:39:56.480 --> 00:39:57.840
It's my treat today.

00:39:57.840 --> 00:40:00.320
You guys can order whatever you want.

00:40:00.640 --> 00:40:01.280
Wei.

00:40:01.680 --> 00:40:03.040
Come on.

00:40:03.040 --> 00:40:04.880
You're not just feeding yourself

00:40:04.880 --> 00:40:06.120
anymore.

00:40:06.480 --> 00:40:08.280
If you're treating us to hotpot,

00:40:08.360 --> 00:40:11.520
shouldn't you ask Jia for permission?

00:40:12.040 --> 00:40:12.720
Caibao.

00:40:13.160 --> 00:40:16.080
Our bro Bao has been single for a long time,

00:40:16.080 --> 00:40:17.840
but he has a high level of awareness.

00:40:17.840 --> 00:40:19.280
Of course.

00:40:19.280 --> 00:40:20.640
Makes sense.

00:40:20.960 --> 00:40:23.280
Let me ask her.

00:40:23.280 --> 00:40:24.240
Jia.

00:40:24.240 --> 00:40:25.240
Why ask me?

00:40:26.160 --> 00:40:27.690
I'm going to rip you off too.

00:40:32.840 --> 00:40:34.080
For this joint test,

00:40:34.800 --> 00:40:36.130
where are you assigned?

00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:37.080
Kashgar.

00:40:40.280 --> 00:40:40.880
Wei.

00:40:41.720 --> 00:40:44.280
Why don't you ask Gu and Qin

00:40:44.280 --> 00:40:45.040
to transfer you back?

00:40:45.040 --> 00:40:46.320
You did so well there.

00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:47.760
They'll definitely agree.

00:40:47.760 --> 00:40:49.760
Yeah, we are short-handed here too.

00:40:49.760 --> 00:40:50.600
Stay.

00:40:51.640 --> 00:40:53.500
I still have work to do back there.

00:40:54.320 --> 00:40:55.920
You have no idea.

00:40:55.920 --> 00:40:57.600
I'm doing great

00:40:57.600 --> 00:40:59.160
in Kashgar now.

00:40:59.160 --> 00:41:01.600
Everyone knows me.

00:41:01.600 --> 00:41:04.640
I'm the technical backbone of the flight control matrix

00:41:04.640 --> 00:41:07.360
and the mainstay of Kashgar Station.

00:41:07.360 --> 00:41:10.880
Also known as the little prince of the Gobi Desert.

00:41:15.640 --> 00:41:17.500
All right, don't pull a long face.

00:41:17.880 --> 00:41:19.760
As for me, no matter where I work

00:41:19.960 --> 00:41:21.160
or what I do,

00:41:21.320 --> 00:41:24.840
I will always be your most reliable support.

00:41:25.760 --> 00:41:26.960
I'd like to propose a toast.

00:41:26.960 --> 00:41:28.440
Here's to the joint debugging and testing,

00:41:28.440 --> 00:41:30.640
and may the Haoyue Mission go smoothly.

00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:31.600
Come on.

00:41:32.800 --> 00:41:33.360
Cheers.

00:41:33.520 --> 00:41:34.440
Smoothly.

00:41:36.840 --> 00:41:38.920
Smoothly.

00:41:38.920 --> 00:41:39.880
Cheers.

00:41:40.720 --> 00:41:41.480
Let's begin.

00:41:41.760 --> 00:41:42.360
Alright.

00:41:43.560 --> 00:41:45.760
First, I will announce an appointment.

00:41:45.960 --> 00:41:48.560
Upon the department's application and leadership's approval,

00:41:48.560 --> 00:41:51.920
Chu Jiajia is promoted to Deputy Chief Designer,

00:41:51.920 --> 00:41:54.080
and will be in charge of Haoyue 5's

00:41:54.080 --> 00:41:56.120
earth-moon orbit flight control phase.

00:41:56.120 --> 00:41:59.000
Great.

00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:00.120
Thank you both.

00:42:00.720 --> 00:42:01.320
Great.

00:42:01.600 --> 00:42:03.600
In addition, Jiang Mengyao and Li Yanyan

00:42:03.600 --> 00:42:05.600
will assist in completing the mission throughout the process.

00:42:05.600 --> 00:42:06.240
Yes, sir.

00:42:06.560 --> 00:42:07.760
Qu Ruonan

00:42:08.160 --> 00:42:11.360
is promoted to the leader of Team A in the flight control department.

00:42:11.360 --> 00:42:13.800
She will be responsible for

00:42:13.800 --> 00:42:15.640
the orbital data plan during the lunar landing process.

00:42:15.640 --> 00:42:18.560
You Xiu and Cai Bo'ao will assist.

00:42:19.920 --> 00:42:20.450
Yes, sir.

00:42:21.160 --> 00:42:23.320
What else? And... And...

00:42:23.640 --> 00:42:25.440
What else? And?

00:42:32.200 --> 00:42:33.120
Ying Ziqi.

00:42:34.240 --> 00:42:34.840
Wu Wei.

00:42:35.160 --> 00:42:37.280
After sampling, you two will be in charge

00:42:37.280 --> 00:42:41.080
of the rendezvous and docking of the ascender and returner.

00:42:48.040 --> 00:42:49.480
He's calling you, Wu Wei.

00:42:56.160 --> 00:42:57.040
Thank you, Mr. Gu.

00:42:57.040 --> 00:42:58.100
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

